Undid revision 993190961 by [[Special:Contributions/Hyderabad22|Hyderabad22]] ([[User talk:Hyderabad22|talk]]) {Disagree.  You're holding Mastriano to a different standard than other nationally known retired military officers, whose pages include their service medals and decorations.  Is there an agenda here?  Reverting.

The citation requests are redundant and not necessary for Mastriano's military service, which was covered by the Indiana Gazette, and has never been in question; Also removed the Giuliani-Covid sentence since there is no evidence he contracted it at Mastriano's meeting, considering that he subsequently attended three other similar meetings later in Michigan, Arizona, and Georgia.  So put it on Giuliani's page where it is more relevant.
Added quote from local pastor in PA33 reflecting a different opinion than the York Daily Record (which is outside PA33) for balance.

Adding Mastriano's service medals and decorations, as is acceptable Wiki practice for senior U.S. military officers and notable enlisted people.  For example, see entries on H.R. McMaster, Raymond Odierno, and David Petraeus, among others.

Removing the "Giuliani catches COVID" passage because it's gratuitous.  There is no evidence that he was infected at that event since Giuliani subsequently did three other public meetings or hearings in Michigan, Georgia, and Arizona that were closer to when his symptoms appeared.
